  "prompt": "What are some shows similar to Leverage?",
  "response": "If you enjoyed watching \"Leverage,\" you might be interested in these TV shows that share similar themes of heists, cons, and team dynamics:\n\n1. **White Collar** \u2013 This series follows Neal Caffrey, a suave, charming con artist, and FBI agent Peter Burke, who work together to catch white-collar criminals.\n\n2. **Burn Notice** \u2013 Centers around former spy Michael Westen, who uses his skills to help those in trouble while trying to uncover who burned him and why.\n\n3. **Person of Interest** \u2013 An ex-CIA operative and a reclusive billionaire work together to prevent violent crimes using a predictive artificial intelligence system.\n\n4. **The Blacklist** \u2013 Follows criminal mastermind Raymond \u201cRed\u201d Reddington as he helps the FBI catch high-profile criminals.\n\n5. **Hustle** \u2013 A British series about a team of con artists who pull off elaborate schemes against morally corrupt targets.\n\n6. **Sneaky Pete** \u2013 Focuses on a con man who, upon leaving prison, takes on the identity of his former cellmate to evade a dangerous gangster.\n\n7. **Psych** \u2013 Follows fake psychic detective Shawn Spencer, who uses his amazing observational skills to solve crimes.\n\n8. **Alias** \u2013 A spy series that follows double agent Sydney Bristow as she deals with the complexities of undercover work.\n\n9. **Mission: Impossible** \u2013 The classic series that involves a team of secret agents who undertake intricate and dangerous missions.\n\nThese shows should provide a mix of thrills, drama, and clever capers akin to what you enjoyed in \"Leverage.\"",
